next cambion before the kobalt had regain all his power. So when he attacked the next cambions I let arrows fly at the kobalt. It took a few arrows but I dropped the kobalt, but during the battle I saw the coward troll run thru the portal.<br><br>Now I continued my trip to the hib side, but I came to an inpass. There was a room full of cambions and to there right was a hall filled with more cambions. Straight ahead I could see an other hall filled with essence shredders or naburite drinkers, hard to tell from a distance. All of these are notorious stealth detectors. I studied the room for a long time tried to find a way around it and came up empty. So I decide to try to go to the Midguard side, even if I had never been there before or how to get there. I know the path would be filled with more stealth detectors, but then I remembered the two Midguards I saw earlier, maybe the path they cleared was still open. As I made my way from room and halls filled with essence shredders and naburite drinkers, I realized that a path had indeed been cleared on my right hand side going into midguard. Then I came to an other inpass, the final path going up into midguard was filled with essence shredders, naburite drinkers and cambions. I studied the situation for a very long time. In one of my excursion up to the platform I saw a group of 4 midguards fight cambions, but alas they where not attacking the cambions blocking my path.  Final after I could not wait any longer and being sure the path behind me had closed, I made my move. I noticed that essence shredders and naburite drinkers where moving much to often for me to try and sneak by, but the cambions would fly in one spot for a bit then patrol again. So if i waited for the far cambion to be near the far wall and the one blocking my path up the ramp had her back to me. There was a small chance that I would be able to sneak by. So I said my prays and attempted this risky maneuver. My prays where answered, I made it past the cambions and it looked like a cambion I had not seen had  been engaged by the Midguard group and died just as I made my way past them. <br><br>The rest of the way up I would see groups of 2 or more fighting the demons in Darkness Falls, but they where all to close to each other for me to engage. As I moved my way up I finally got to room that was empty. Having remembered that I had seen a kobalt/dwarf team fighting in the room previous I decide to dispatch the world of one of them. This group was much smarter that the first, they would wait for the kobalt to regain all its power. The dwarf was more experience that I, but the kobalt seem to be equal to me in experience. So the kobalt would be my next victim. It took a few arrows to kill the kobalt again, because he was able to heal a few times. But I was able to drop it, but soon after the dwarf killed its target and made its way to me. Again my  luck held out, just as he made his way into my room I was able to stealth again.<br><br>I continued to stealth and explore, along the way I killed a very young troll in hopes to luring one of his comrades. It was not my intention to kill him since I knew trolls cold take a beating, but look like the relics we have recently capture made my shot stronger than I taught it would be. His comrade did not come. It looked like he was more interested in buying stuff from the merchants than helping a comrade. I made my way down again a saw another very young midguard, but he was a sheather, so a danger to me so I had to kill him. I saw two more young but experienced mids, enough to be a small challenge. So I showed them what Darkness Falls dirt taste like. <br><br>Then I explored more saw trolls that would be too risky for me to kill. I went back to my old spot where the dwarf/kobalt team had been. There was now a group of 5 midguard there and fighting cambions only one at the time. Not once did they drop below 3/4 life, they were cowards taking no risk. they where all more or as experience as I except for one. I could tell that the norse was very close to being my equal but not quit there. He was not doing much in the battles, a rare heal during and some after the battle was over. So I tried to take him out, dang it takes a lot of arrows to drop a healer. But I was able to. I tried to get away but just before I was able to stealth a smelly troll farted on me and I was poisoned. So I made a run for the portal a long ways off. but on the way I angered two demons. So i had to fight them, but I chose a spot that hopefully the midguard would take a few second longer to find me. I was able to kill both demons with only a fraction of life remaining in me. Also stealthed just as a kobalt turned the corner. Again lady luck was shining on me, from what I could tell  3 of the midguards stayed to fight the cambion. They sent the kobalt after me and he was also jumped by two demons (I saw two sacks of coins on the ground). I was able to kill my two demons just before he killed his and stealth. I rested and explored some more, the group of 5 had called  a group of 4 more to them and I knew it was time to call it a night. So I made my way to find a hiding place to sleep. On my way I saw a very young midguard caster. It did hurt me to kill him but I taught his death would disrupt the groups below for a few minutes while I slept.<br><br>Yours <br>Nimitz<br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uapo44.showPublicProfile?language=EN>apo44</A> at: 4/22/02 2:13:16 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Wamba</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/22/02 1:51:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1067.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Heh-heh</span><hr size=1> Nimitz, this story is 