d><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Heh-heh</span><hr size=1> This is a very cool strory Nim, I bet your having  a great time, but on the prey side of the story, it makes me shiver.<br>I wish you would tell us about those who had defeated you so we could learn how to defend ourselves.<br>Archers are uber because they can stealth, distance attack, critic and re-stealth. (or use a speed buff for kobolts)<br>Stealth: they can choose who, when and where they attack. <br>             Who: a lower level ( I was ALWAYS attacked by an orange or red)<br>              When: by surprize when I have just engage a mob or when I'm sitting after a fight)<br>             Where: in the back, where my shield connot protect me.<br>Distance attack: I never was able to catch an archer unless someone casts a root on him.<br>Critics: with 2 arrows I loose half my hit points<br>Re-stealth: the usual tactic used on me is: to pull 2 arrows, run away and re-stealth, then come back later to finish me.<br><br>Now, anyone has an idea how I could defend myself against archers??? Or am I in this game only to amuse archers?<br>At least assassin's attacks are toe to toe and I have a chance to grab them by the belt and to spank their little kobolt's buttocks real hard.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uaroqua.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aroqua</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/23/02 10:56:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1067.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Heh-heh</span><hr size=1> 1 way to defend is after you get hit with first shot is to engage the archer with your shield ability. This will block most all of the next arrows. Once we are enaged it takes away the crit shot. This shot is take away as well if you walk around in combat mode it seems.<br><br>Aro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/udunkar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dunkar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/23/02 11:07:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1067.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Archers</span><hr size=1> Best defense for archers are Infiltrators, keep one handy in your back pocket...  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Dunkar Donuts <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/unizudn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nizudn</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Bruce</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/23/02 4:18:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1067.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A report from behinde enemy lines.</span><hr size=1> I'm speaking from the perspective of my level 24 archer here...<br><br>I'm actually not sure how <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> directly</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> helpful an infiltrator would be against archers. I do agree that they can kick an archers butt if they find them... However, it seems like &quot;detect hidden&quot; does not really work as well as advertised and many (most?) archers have attact range that will be outside of detection range. <br><br>I'm still a super-archer-noob, but I seem to see infiltrators at just about the same time they see me or maybe just a little bit latter. This is with about half my level in stealth right now. Having an inf nearby would be a good thing, but you may have to absorb an arrow or two before the inf can do their job.<br><br>What I think an infiltrator can really do well for you is act as a human... er... toon... watchdog. I think that many archers will move on to greener pastures rather then risk an unfortunate death to a lurking infiltrator... popping into view once in a while is a good way to scare off some folks. It's a lot like Dia said, archers can pick thier targets and are generally fairly careful. If I KNOW there is a stealthed character around, that changes the odds considerably.<br><br>Dia has already covered most of the &quot;archer secrets&quot; that I have heard before. It is very difficult to be completely safe from a patient archer. If the archer decides to plink away at you, there is really no alternative other then to go on the offensive and try to track them down. They can dish the damage far faster then a regular tank can heal especially when the tank cannot ever sit or leave combat mode.<br><br>My (admittedly) uninformed opinion.<br>Cheers, <p>Niz, Tavik, etc...<BR>Forgotten Truth</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ubasilicus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Basilicus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/23/02 5:51:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1067.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A report from behinde enemy lines.</span><hr size=1> Don't know how well this applies to Albion, but here is what I did to win against archers with my Mid Healer.<br><br>After I took the first hit, I immediately started casting stun. I use stun because it seems to stick faster than anything else. I take another hit or 2 then get stun off, followed by a mez. Then I heal myself up, cast another mez, then rush in for the attack. <br><br>Maybe was a fluke thing but sure worked for me.<br><br>Basilicus<br>28 Middie Healer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/udunkar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dunkar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/23/02 11:54:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1067.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Detect Hidden</span><hr size=1> Have seen it go both ways, here's some examples...<br><br>Infiltrator #1 (Lets call him Dalth):<br>Groupmate:  Hey Dalth, there is a Hunter on the far side of the MF1, try to find him.<br><br>Dalth:  K, brb.<br><br>...a few minutes later...<br><br>Dalth:  Ack!  What killed ya?<br><br>Groupmate:  That archer I told you to find.....<br><br>Infiltrator #2 (All the other Infiltrators)<br><br>Dalth to other Inf:  Hey man, just saw a Norse Hunter outside of MF1, killed my groupmate.<br><br>...turn around to see the Hunter fall lifeless...<br><br>Other Inf:  You mean this one?<br><br>Some peopel have it, some don't.  Personally, I just run around like a chicken with his head cut off hoping to trip over them by accident. <br><br>As I advance in levels, I have noticed an increase in my base detect hidden radius against much higher levels of stealth.  With Dunkar I would have to be standing right next to Nimitz to see him, but Dalth has a larger detection range.  During todays RP Swap in Emain, I was able to see Artemes (Lvl 50 Inf w/52 Stealth) from about 1.5 horse lengths.  Willing to bet as I progress in levels that range will increase.  <br><br>As for the Assassin/Archer engagements, I think I have the hang of it.  Detected Kris down in front of the keep we were defending, so I made a bee-line for her.  Took a split second to choice the precise poisons for the job at hand, nothing so bold as a DoT or Disease, something subtle...a snare.  <br><br>Made my final approach, she's still there.  Hit the /stick command to make sure I don't fluff this up, she still there and it looks like she is about to shoot someone.  (*started thinking how surprised she will be as I pop out of no where with weapons flying).  Launch my attack and success!  You performed Perferate Artery perfectly!  Elated I nailed the follow-up style, and nothing happened.  Thinking it was a lag spike I hit it again, and again, and again...but all I see is a silly message saying &quot;You can't perform that command while laying down&quot;.  Laying down?  Impossible, I was just attacking someone.  That is when I noticed the bright red message indicating Kris has him me for 1040 points, type /release you schmuck cause you DEAD!  <br><br>Morale of the story, as a stealther if you can see them and they are purple, chances are they saw you a long time ago and had enough time to set up a perfect close quarters Crit Strike to your left eyeball.<br><br>Dalth, Doormat to the World <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/usareshft.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saresh FT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/24/02 1:51:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1067.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Detect Hidden</span><hr size=1> Thats ok Dalth.... Im there with ya.  Most of my PVP has been by blind luck.  I just kind of position myself where I think people will hide/travel.<br><br>I find most people in PVP are like cattle.... predictable in their actions.   <br><br>Youll see that the majority of people use the same hiding places or same travel paths.  But its their reaction that makes it all exciting.  Everyone has a different reaction.... some freeze up, some flee, and some turn around and go into kick-your-ass mode.<br><br>Im a freezer.... my fingers usually hit the wrong keys or im in the wrong hotkey bank <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><BR>Saresh  LvL 35 Infiltrator<BR>Numms  LvL 12 Cleric<BR>Miradia  LvL 13 Wizardess<BR>Forgotten Truth (Palomides)<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ufarmelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Farmelle</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.horsford.force9.co.uk/Icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/24/02 3:29:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1067.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Detect Hidden</span><hr size=1> I have the advantage of Simmy.  If an archer attacks me he HAS to kill me.  I also have encrust eyes.  My tactic in the BG so far is wait for the archer to hit me when I have no target selected and encrust them.  They can't hit me again unless they are close.  If they are close then Simmy is on them by the time they have got their second shot off.  Then they take a dirt nap.<br><br>Best one I have had so far is Simmy going 'missing', then I got 22rps.  Didn't even notice that I had been hit.<br><br>Other little hints.  Keep moving.  If you are not moving or casting then stay in combat mode as it greatly reduces the chance to crit.  NEVER sit down to heal or med.<br><br>Farmelle 'One hit wonder' VonFolger <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bforgottentruthforeignlegion.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=belsader>Belsader</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/25/02 10:23:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1067.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Detect Hidden</span><hr size=1> Granted, my experience as a stealth class in RvR is pretty limited (newbie BG!) -- I do have a fair amount of experience as a smite cleric on Morgan Le Fey.  (17k RP's or thereabouts, and I quit playing the character last year)<br><br>For the caster classes, a couple recommendations.  First is hardware believe it or not -- you can really benefit from macros with a Nostromo N50 gamepad.  Curiosity (Iska on MLF) had a great anti-archer macro setup that wizzies could use as well.  With her theurgist, she had a macro that auto-faced, quick-cast a nuke and then cast a pet.  If the archer was in nuke range, he was interrupted right away.  If out of nuke range, the pet would be quick cast instead since it has a slightly longer range.  Either is typically enough to convince an archer type to move on -- you can't shoot with a pet beating on you, and if you are in nuke range you are toast as well (since the nukes are faster).  If they stayed to fight after being nuked or with a pet on them they were typically toast.<br><br>Did this always work?  Nope -- but it at least gives a cloth wearer a 50/50 chance.  You can do the same thing without a macro, but it's definitely tougher.  Wizzies can exchange a pet for a bolt with even better results.  We were at least playing with a defensive armsman at the time, who could block arrows and run down the archers ...<br><br>For myself (the smite cleric) I'd depend on insta-heal and charging the target.  If I could get into base-line smite range (the 3 second casts) they probably weren't going to get away.  In DF this would be more problematical unfortunately, since in RvR you are (or at least should be) always ready for an attack.  In DF this isn't the case, unless you have had some death spam to prepare with ...<br><br>For assassins ... you have the good fortune of being Albion, you don't want to mess with a smite cleric.  ;-)  I don't think I ever sat down long enough for a PA to land on me while sitting, and I was high enough level for a PA not to be able to kill me in one shot.  Insta, mez, heal self, cure poison, nuke, stun, nuke, nuke -- free RP's.  :-)  Use a lot of caution when fighting mid healers for the same reason, even if they can't nuke.  (This is pretty obvious, but what the heck...maybe someone didn't know.)  Granted, this was before the boost to points for assassin classes, they are probably more formidable now.  I want to kill healers myself, so I'm going to try a spec that's light on poison and very heavy on crit/thrust.<br><br>Now for my story ...<br><br>In the newbie BG, a bunch of mids managed to stage a breakout and push the albion forces back when they were camping the mid PK.  A lot of deaths on both sides, but the mids managed to wipe out the albions -- so they were recovering.  The single healer was rezzing the fallen ...<br><br>So, the mids (for some reason) were in 3 slightly spread out groups.  I'd already killed the only shadowblade (who had low stealth anyway) so I wasn't too concerned about being detected -- he hadn't been rez'd yet.  The healer was just slightly outside the guard aggro range ... sitting down to regain mana.  heh.  heh.<br><br>So, I zig-zagged between the two other middy groups.  Stand in front of the healer sitting down, land the PA -- 99% dead.  One style lands the finishing hit.  Unfortunately, my ISP started having problems right at that time or I would have gotten away cleanly ... I almost got away ANYWAY it caught them by surprise so badly.  (I also ditched my ISP the next morning I was so ticked off ... now I have cablemodem.)  A caster got a bolt off just as I stealthed, and uncovered me -- otherwise it would have been a totally clean kill.  However -- that was the only healer.  I'm sure I messed them up a bit.  :-)<br><br>Moral of the story?  I had passed up several sure rez-kills because I wanted to take out the healer and I didn't want to give away the fact that I was there.  People dropping dead all around you tend to do that.  The beauty of being a stealth class is that you decide when and where the fight is going to begin, and you do it with surprise.  (Obviously, these were newbies ... but they should have been a lot more cautious).  <br><br>General advice, especially for folks new to RvR:  If you are going to sit down, do it behind guard aggro range.  Group with a minstrel and only sit for a few seconds at a time -- keep moving and assassins don't have time to line up a PA.  Keep bladeturn up (for casters always, for others group with a theurgist) and that will negate an archers crit shot.  Keep moving anyway, the archers can't land a crit if you are out of range).  Stick together in a group -- even if you are chasing down single enemies, because if you disperse, you are in trouble.  Know the area you are fighting in, because when you DO get dispersed, you need to have a place to meet up again as quickly as you can.  Non-stealth classes can't RvR effectively alone, but in a group, they can gank people for hours.  :-)<br><br>If you are going on a grey-ganking session in Odins or Emain, the not splitting up part is especially important.  At some point, the people you are ganking are going to whine for help and you'll get a big force after you.  (I'm assuming this still happens -- maybe with DF in the game the frontiers are dead).  Typically even the higher level groups will split up in 3's or 4's to spread out to find you ... you can roll the small groups, and then move again.  Keep moving and you can repeat until you have them bottled up at the port fort.  (It's kind of sad to see a single group of high 40's -&gt; 50's have a few dozen mids or hibs bottled up scared to come out when they are uncoordinated).<br><br>Ok, that's enough.  Too long as it is.  Now go out and kill somebody.  :-)<br><br>--Belsader, 24 Infiltrator Palomides<br>--Belsarius, 42 Smite Cleric, MLF<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bforgottentruthforeignlegion.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=curiosity>Curiosity</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/25/02 11:28:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1067.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Detect Hidden</span><hr size=1> Belsader is right the macro gamepad had really helped me out as a caster in RvR (43 Theurgist).  He mentioned my tactic for when I was solo or in a small group.  Since I could cast so fast (2 sec ice spells) once I got the archer interrupted (providing he was in my range) I could get more casts in before he could get his bow up and finish him.  Usually they were not in my range though and the backup pet would at least be there to scare them off.  <br><br>However when I hunted in larger well organized groups I used a different macro.  Instead of blasting the archer I would try to mez or root them then the pet was last resort there too.  It was usually more detrimental to my health but there was more of an assurance the group could get the archer when they were on ice.  Theurg Mez was always kind of pointless, the range was too short to use effectively and it had a 1 sec longer cast time than root.  However it couldn't hurt to add it to the macro since my macros were more of a &quot;If.. then&quot;  sort of setup.  Macro would /face then quickcast and then hit Mez, Root, and pet quickly so that whatever was in range first would get cast then the rest was up to me.  <br><br>Just my old tactics, I know the game has changed a bit since I last played Iska on Morgan Le Fay but I only see these as getting better since they put in the faster casting dex boost.  When I had max dex buffs on I was a killing machine <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Bel told me to put in my realm point score though I don't think it is very impressive anymore since months have passed.  My old character should still be on the top 25 list on the herald but I just looked and for some reason she isn't listed there.  It is possible I need to log her back in and kill a few more enemies before I will get back on the list.  She has not been logged on since I canceled my account back around December.  I have approx 52,000 rpts.  Guessing mind you so give or take 1,000.<br><br>--Curiosity, 24 Minstrel Palomides<br>--Iska, 43 Theurgist MLF <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub10.ezboard.com